✅ 3. Normalization to 3NF
All entities are:

1NF: Atomic values (no repeating groups)

2NF: No partial dependencies (since PKs are single-column or composite with full dependency)

3NF: No transitive dependencies (all non-key attributes depend only on the PK)

 Example FDs:
BookID → Title, Author, ISBN, Publisher, YearPublished, Genre, CopiesAvailable

MemberID → Name, Email, Phone, Address, MembershipDate

LoanID → BookID, MemberID, LoanDate, DueDate, ReturnDate

StaffID → Name, Email, Role, HireDate

All are in 3NF ✅

✅ 4. SQL CREATE TABLE Scripts

Book Table
CREATE TABLE Book (
    BookID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    Author VARCHAR(255),
    ISBN VARCHAR(20) UNIQUE,
    Publisher VARCHAR(100),
    YearPublished INT,
    Genre VARCHAR(100),
    CopiesAvailable INT DEFAULT 0
);

Member Table
CREATE TABLE Member (
    MemberID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    Email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
    Phone VARCHAR(20),
    Address VARCHAR(255),
    MembershipDate DATE
);

Loan Table
CREATE TABLE Loan (
    LoanID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    BookID INT,
    MemberID INT,
    LoanDate DATE NOT NULL,
    DueDate DATE NOT NULL,
    ReturnDate DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (BookID) REFERENCES Book(BookID),
    FOREIGN KEY (MemberID) REFERENCES Member(MemberID)
);

Staff Table
CREATE TABLE Staff (
    StaffID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    Email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
    Role VARCHAR(100),
    HireDate DATE
);
